    <h1>National Cadet Corps - NCC</h1>
    <p class="lead">The National Cadet Corps (NCC) is a premier youth organization in India that aims to develop character, discipline, leadership, and a spirit of adventure among the youth. The NCC Wing is a division of the NCC that focuses on providing opportunities for cadets to serve the nation and develop their personality through various activities.</p>

    <h2>Objectives</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Develop qualities of character, courage, discipline, and leadership.</li>
      <li>Provide basic military training and foster a sense of patriotism.</li>
      <li>Develop a spirit of adventure and outdoor activities.</li>
      <li>Instill the values of selfless service and social responsibility.</li>
      <li>Promote national integration and unity among the youth.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Activities</h2>
    <p>The NCC Wing organizes a wide range of activities to achieve its objectives. These include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Drill and weapon training</li>
      <li>Camping and trekking</li>
      <li>Community service</li>
      <li>Disaster management</li>
      <li>Leadership development programs</li>
      <li>Health and wellness campaigns</li>
      <li>Social awareness programs</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Benefits</h2>
    <p>Participating in the NCC Wing offers numerous benefits to cadets, including:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Leadership development</li>
      <li>Enhanced discipline and time management skills</li>
      <li>Opportunities for adventure and outdoor activities</li>
      <li>Physical fitness and self-defense training</li>
      <li>Scholarship opportunities</li>
      <li>Exposure to social issues and community service</li>
      <li>Preference in various government job selections</li>
    </ul>
